BugReports: https://github.com/ehrlinger/hvtiPropensityScores/issues
Description: Propensity score estimation, matching, and inverse-probability
    treatment weighting (IPTW) for clinical investigations within The Heart
    & Vascular Institute (HVTI) at the Cleveland Clinic. Provides a consistent
    two-step workflow — construct a scored/weighted dataset with a `ps_*()`
    function, then inspect or pass results downstream — with standardised
    balance diagnostics (SMD tables, effective N) compatible with
    `hvtiPlotR::hv_mirror_hist()` and `hvtiPlotR::hv_balance()`.
